name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, the dedicated members of @LAVetAffairs accomplished a lot, including dedicating the Southwest Louisiana Veterans Cemetery, launched the Project LOVE letter-writing campaign, and continued to support student veterans through the LaVetCorps program. #lagov  https://t.co/z8itPWdQby

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, the outstanding men and women of the @LANationalGuard were instrumental in our fight against COVID-19 and our recovery from a relentless hurricane season. In addition to service at home, over 2,000 of Louisiana’s guardsmen were deployed. #lagov  https://t.co/GhlONc6izj

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, the team at @LDWF finished the restoration of Queen Bess Island, renovated the Bussey Brake Reservoir in Morehouse Parish, and started distributing initial payments of more than $14 million in CARES Act funding to charter and commercial fishing communities. #lagov  https://t.co/v5sCcZ7fIL

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, the dedicated men and women at @LouisianaDCFS sheltered over 18,000 people during hurricane season, distributed pandemic EBT to the families of 478,112 children, and had the 4th highest number of adoptions in state history. #lagov  https://t.co/Rc1l7lhAam

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, in addition to hurricane response efforts, the dedicated men and women at @LouisianaCPRA advanced 112 projects vital to our coast and, under an order signed by the Governor, established the Climate Initiatives Task Force. #lagov  https://t.co/4KHuilE4cJ

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Congratulations to @RaginCajunsFB on winning the SERVPO First Responders Bowl and for what has been a truly remarkable season. Coach Napier, his players and every member of the Ragin’ Cajun community should be proud of what they accomplished this year. #lagov #GeauxCajuns

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: We are saddened to hear of the loss of Vic Stelly. Vic served dutifully during his 16 year tenure in the Louisiana House of Representatives and later as a member of the Board of Regents. Please join @FirstLadyOfLA and me in praying for his family and friends. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: .@FirstLadyOfLA and I would like to wish a Happy Kwanzaa to everyone who is celebrating today. #lagov #Kwanzaa  https://t.co/N6Nrsdeb00

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Merry Christmas, Louisiana. 🎄#lagov  https://t.co/KIwErkictM

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year, @FirstLadyOfLA and I asked our friends from the @McNeese and @Grambling1901 choirs to join us in wishing all of Louisiana a very safe, healthy, and Merry Christmas! #lagov  Watch here:  https://t.co/AcBgTnZVL2

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: As we look back at what has been a very hard year, I want to thank the people of Louisiana for their resilience and dedication to each other. 2020 proved just how tough Louisianans are and I‘m thankful for their ability to make it through every challenge this year brought. #lagov  https://t.co/3TpBjtvmpX

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Please join @FirstLadyOfLA and me in praying for congressman elect Letlow as he continues his fight against COVID-19. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year has been tragic and sad and we finally have the hope of better therapeutics and a vaccine, which means the end of the pandemic is in our sights. Now is not the time to let down our guard simply because it is Christmas or New Year’s Eve. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: I cannot stress this enough: the holidays this year cannot look the same as they have in previous years. Having parties where people from various households gather together, especially indoors, is dangerous and could lead to the spread of COVID and the loss of loved ones. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Everyone is at risk, but those who are 65 or older or who have health conditions that make it more likely that they will have severe COVID complications should be incredibly careful in the coming days and should avoid any indoor place where there is not universal masking. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Just this week, we reported the highest number of deaths since July. Aggressive mitigation is recommended by Louisiana’s public health experts and the White House Coronavirus Task Force, and it is critical that everyone take every action to slow the spread of COVID. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: While we have seen minor improvements, no one should feel good about our current COVID situation in Louisiana. We have too many new cases, too many people in the hospital and, sadly, too many Louisianans continue to die of this illness. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Today, I extended my modified Phase Two order, including Louisiana’s statewide mask mandate, to January 13, 2021, as hospitalizations have exceeded the level reached during the second surge in July.  https://t.co/CAaGuAHJUV #lagov  https://t.co/rP0Vxu098E

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: I am proud to welcome this new fulfillment center to Louisiana, and I look forward to Amazon’s continued investment in our great state. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This 1 million-square-foot fulfillment center will not only prove to be a tremendous asset for all of Louisiana, but the project also will create 500 full-time jobs on-site, and spur the growth of other jobs in Acadiana. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: You don’t become the world’s largest online retailer without making a series of well-reasoned strategic investments, and Amazon’s selection of Carencro for its new fulfillment center is a testament to this. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Today, I announced that @amazon will open its first Louisiana fulfillment center in the city of Carencro. The company will make a $100 million capital investment and create 500 direct jobs with an annual payroll of more than $16 million.  https://t.co/Rmmzql3uGF #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: Today at 11:30 a.m., Gov. Edwards will participate in a large economic development announcement.  #lagov  ⏰: 11:30 a.m. 🎥:  https://t.co/kLKbbKZ6vW 💻:  https://t.co/vSvlRpr0Dy

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: As the Holidays take full swing wearing a mask is one of the most important things we can do to protect ourselves and others. They only work if we wear them correctly, so do it right and help stop the spread of COVID this Christmas. #lagov  https://t.co/KV846DPyMQ

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This holiday season, let’s show the people we love how much we care about them by acting responsibly and protecting them from COVID-19. This Christmas, let’s spread cheer, not COVID. #lagov  https://t.co/PWZLVHMuPM

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: COVID-19 is a very real threat. We’ve lost more than 7,000 Louisianans to this virus—Louisianans who were parents, siblings, aunts and uncles, and friends. Let’s make the right choices as we celebrate the holidays this year. Our actions will save lives. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: The number of people lost to COVID-19 in 9 months surpasses the number of people lost to accidents, strokes, and diabetes in all of 2017. The impact COVID has had on Louisiana is real and we all need to work together to fight it. #lagov

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: This year has been hard and although the holidays are a time for us to be thankful and joyous, they can also be difficult for many. Please use these resources if you need them and know that you aren’t alone this holiday season. #lagov  https://t.co/L52GS6WOAW

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: While we plan how to celebrate the holidays please be aware of the risks. How we celebrate will determine how our fight against COVID will look from here on out. We owe it to our healthcare heroes, our vulnerable population and each other to act responsibly and safely. #lagov  https://t.co/nvU1qjjYNw

name: John Bel Edwards
tweet: The decisions that you make and the way you celebrate the holidays this year will determine whether you, your family, and people you don’t even know will be at high risk of getting COVID-19. #lagov  https://t.co/uWcy6Q0RT2
